Deloitte Productivity Cleaning Script

Library

library(tidyverse)
library(janitor)
library(readxl)
library(here)

Functions

multiplesheets <- function(fname) {
   
  # getting info about all excel sheets
  sheets <- readxl::excel_sheets(fname)
  tibble <- lapply(sheets, function(x) readxl::read_excel(fname, sheet = x))
  data_frame <- lapply(tibble, as.data.frame)
    
  # assigning names to data frames
  names(data_frame) <- sheets
    
  # print data frame
  print(data_frame)
}
  
# specifying the path name

Source data are mid-year estimates. Prior to 1971 from Source #4, Table UK.11 (Labour market: employment) with an adjustment to take account of redistribution of employment between manufacturing and other industries in the transition from SIC 1948 to SIC 1968 in 1959.
9  Hours splits, quarterly series: between 1984q1 and 1993q4, taken from Source #3, Table 18a (Average actual weekly hours of work by industry sector - all persons). 1                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Date of Publication: 05 October 2018
2                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   <NA>
3                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Notes
4  This workbook provides estimates, for each industry section in each NUTS1 region, of Seasonally Adjusted (SA) Productivity Hours and Jobs, as well as Output per Hour and Output per Job. The methodology employed differs to that used to produce Productivity Hours in our "Productivity Jobs, productivity hours, market sector workers, market sector hours" tables, and Output per Hour in our "Labour Productivity: Tables 1 to 10 and R1" tables. For more information about the methodology, please see the article released on the same day as this dataset.
5                                                                       UK labour productivity estimates in this dataset may not replicate those produced in the "Labour Productivity: Tables 1 to 10 and R1" due to methodological differences in the calculation of productivity jobs and hours, as well as differences between the regional GVA figures (from which the UK totals of this dataset are taken) and the UK GVA figures in the latest Quarterly National Accounts (from which the estimates in "Labour Productivity: Tables 1 to 10 and R1" are derived).
